@node INT "Why then another utility ?  There's already enough on the Aminet !"


The  notification  is  an AmigaOS feature that can signal a task when a file or
directory is modified.


 *  MultiNotify installs notifications on the files or directories you want and
    execute  any  AmigaDOS  command  when  the file or directory in question is
    modified.


 *  It has a nice Triton graphical user interface and is a commodity.  (You can
    very easyli manipulate it with the commodities Exchange program.)

    @{b}@{" Triton " link REA} is Copyrighted (c) by Stefan Zeiger.@{ub}


 *  You  can  select the files to start the notification on and the commands to
    execute with an Asl Filerequester.  (The standard filerequester of AmigaOS)

@endnode



