@node TRA "Translations of MultiNotify"

If  there  isen't  a  translation  for  your  native  language  you  can make a
translation of the documentation and the catalog yourself.

@{b}Please   don't  release  the  translations  on  Aminet  directly.@{ub}   Send  these
translations  to the @{" Author " link AUT} per e-mail or on a simple double density floppy.
The  versions and other stuff of the files will be checked, eventually modified
and then released on the Aminet as separate archives.


@{b}If  the  translations already exists@{ub} you should be able to find them on Aminet.
They are typically called:

    MultiNotify@{b}ITA@{ub}.lha      for the @{i}italian@{ui} version
    MultiNotify@{b}NOR@{ub}.lha      for the @{i}norvegian@{ui} version...
    MultiNotify@{b}GRE@{ub}.lha      for the @{i}greek@{ui} version


Each  archive  should  contain  a valid catalog file for the current version of
MultiNotify  and  a  guide file.  @{b}Note:  at the time I write these lines, these
archives don't exist.@{ub}

@endnode



